{{Quote|I never really identified as just a witch. I'm an 11th-generation root worker and midwife.|Jennifer Kale|If I Can't Reach You / Let My Song Teach You}}
'''Jennifer "Jen" Kale''' is a witch specializing in potions, a beauty guru, social media influencer, and owner of [[Kale Kare]]. Kale had her powers bound by [[Agatha Harkness]], though she believed a doctor was to blame. Over a century later, in [[2026]], Kale was approached by Harkness to join her [[Agatha Harkness' Coven|coven]] to walk the [[Witches' Road]]. Hoping to regain her powers, Kale accepted. Enduring a series of harrowing trials, Kale soon learned the mysterious teenager accompanying them was [[Billy Maximoff]], a son of [[Scarlet Witch]]. As they approached the end of the road, Kale was left as one of the only survivors. In the [[Green Witch Trial|last trial]], she learned that it was Harkness who bound her. Infuriated, Kale freed herself by renouncing Harkness and thus regaining her powers. Exiting the Road and emerging in [[Westview]], Kale flew away.

==Biography==
===Early Life===
Jennifer Kale is the eleventh generation of her family, who were rootworkers, midwives, and witches. Kale specialized in [[Magic#Alchemy|alchemy]], also known as potions, a branch of witchcraft that specialized in creating potions, which Kale used to heal others.{{Ref|AAA102}}{{Ref|AAA108}}

===Losing Her Powers===
{{Quote|How were you bound?"<br>"I was invited to the brand-new Obstetrics Association of Greater [[Boston]]. To share my expertise. It was a trap. I still don't know how [[Doctor (Torturer)|he]] did it. Bound me without magick. So much for 'do no harm'.|[[Alice Wu-Gulliver]] and Jennifer Kale|If I Can't Reach You / Let My Song Teach You}}
In the [[1920s]], Kale was invited to the Obstetrics Association of Greater Boston to share her knowledge. However, while she was there, she was bound, causing her to lose access to her [[magic]]. Kale believed a [[Doctor (Torturer)|male doctor]] bound her, but wondered how he had done so without any magical ability of his own.{{Ref|AAA102}}{{Ref|AAA103}}{{Ref|AAA104}}

===Kale Kare===
Kale founded a beauty brand called [[Kale Kare]] based in [[Westview]], [[New Jersey]]. Kale also became a celebrity, widely known for her work. However, Kale mislabeled her products by adding petroleum to them and lying about their naturalness, which resulted in some customers suffering from burns and even requiring skin grafts, which landed her in several legal troubles.{{Ref|AAA102}}{{Ref|AAA103}}

===The Witches' Road===
{{Rewrite|Billy should be referred to as "Teen" until Jen herself learns the truth, links should be the full name, and links should repeat in every subsection}}
==== [[Search for Coven Members#Jennifer Kale|Recruited by Agatha Harkness]] ====
In late [[2026]], Kale was visited by an old aquaintance of hers, [[Agatha Harkness]] and [[Wiccan|Teen]], Kale was their target [[:Category:Potions Witches|potions witch]]. Jennifer was helping some customers, who quickly left when they saw Harkness who purposely scared them off. Harkness went straight to the point and told Kale about their plan to walk the Witches' Road. Agatha tried to convince her by talking about the binding spell on her the past century. Maximoff then chimed in, saying she looked great for her age. The two bickered about their past before Harkness stormed off. Maximoff then took his turn, saying how he loved her Instagram, thanking her for minimizing the size of his pores.

Kale asked who he was, remarking how he could be another child sacrifice, specifically referring to Harkness' past. Maximoff then brought up Kale Kare's legal troubles and how people were getting injured. This intrigued Harkness, who started mocking her again. Kale defended herself, but Maximoff talked about the penalties like five years in prison, but then you add on her eight-hundred counts of it. Maximoff then joined in mocking her, saying it would not be a problem for a powered witch. This made Kale snap, saying she had tried everything to unbind herself. Maximoff simply said she had tried everything but the [[Witches' Road]]. Maximoff then handed her an address and said if she vcalued her freedom, she should join them later that day.

Later on that same day, Kale was the first one to arrive at Agatha's [[Agnes O'Connor's House|house]], which initially scared her. Soon the other coven members started to arrive, [[Lilia Calderu]], who exclaimed the term High Priestess at Kale, then came [[Alice Wu-Gulliver]]. The group realized they did not have a green witch, Harkness tried to shake them off, but Kale argued it was necessary. Harkness recruited [[Sharon Davis]] and the witches performed [[Ballad of the Witches' Road]] to conjure it. When no gate appeared, as per her scheme, Harkness blamed her coven and tried to bait them into attacking her so she could steal their power. The gate is opened and the coven barely escapes from the [[Salem Seven]].{{Ref|AAA102}}

====[[Potions Witch Trial]]====
The group entered the road and removed their shoes out of respect for the road, they soon started their walk. As they walked the Road, the coven discussed their situation, wondering what they would be up against for their trials. Believing [[Agatha Harkness|Harkness]] had already walked the Road, they asked her, so she answered that each trial would test their respective skills. The coven learned of the sigil put on Teen, which Harkness knew nothing about, and returned focus to reaching the end of the Road. After they nearly lost Davis to quicksand, Harkness reminded the coven that the first rule was to never step off of the Road.

The [[Agatha Harkness' Coven|coven]] turned around to see a [[Witches' Road Beach House|mansion]] appear on the [[Witches' Road]]. Once the coven was inside, they noticed their clothes had been changed to resemble a coastal chic style. The first trial began with the coven all drinking a bottle of wine that was provided for them, Kale was unknowingly posioned along with her coven, their faces became swollen except for Harkness. Once the swelling went down, Kale was able to deduce that they had been poisoned by [[Alewife's Revenge]]. [[Sharon Davis|Davis]] began to hallucinate which prompted the coven to act fast.

Kale needed to brew an antidote for them, being their [[:Category:Potions Witches|potions witch]]. Kale instructed the coven with the ingredients she required to brew the potion, one of which was frankincense, Wu-Gulliver and Maximoff went to go retrieve it and the other was zooplankton, with Harkness and [[Lilia Calderu]] searching for it. While preparing the potion, Kale recalled another ingridient and went to retrieve Eye of Newt. However, when she returned, she experienced a hallucination of the [[Doctor (Torturer)/Witches' Road|Doctor]] in front of the sink, the Doctor pushed her head into the sink and tried to drown her. When the hallucinations wears off, the coven returned with the missing ingridients.

They gave Kale the ingredients only to notice that the house began to flood. They had to work quickly and carried Davis into the kitchen as Kale used the sink as a cauldron. As they put the ingredients in, Kale told Maximoff to stir counter-clockwise, but had to clarify that meant to the left. Suddenly, Harkness started hallucinating and crying. When she came to, they rushed her to put a strand of her hair in the potion. Once the potion was mixed, Maximoff and the others held hands as Kale explained that once their intentions were aligned, the potion would glow cerulean. Wu-Gulliver noted that it was green and asked if that was the color. Maximoff told her it was blue. They then realized something went wrong. As Kale thought further, she realized she missed a step: they needed the blood of the unpoisoned. Harkness then took a knife and sliced Maximoff's hand, allowing blood to drip into the potion. It soon turned green.

Passing the test, the oven opened up for them to escape as water rushed in, and although Calderu advised them against going in, due to a friend of her perishing this way, they decided to anyways. Though most of the coven were able to drink it in time, they were unable to save [[Sharon Davis]], who died as they escaped the trial through the oven.{{Ref|AAA103}}

====Summoning a Green Witch====
Following the death of Mrs. Davis, the coven decided it was necessary to find a substitute Green Witch, but Harkness argued against this, informing her coven that she was the only witch that made it out of the Road last time. Harkness suggested they summon a new green witch. Using [[Teen]]'s spell book,  Kale wished for the new member to be pleasant looking they performed an incantation, and summoned [[Rio Vidal]], who burst out of Davis' grave. The new member identified herself as not just ''a'' Green Witch, but ''the'' Green Witch. With Vidal tagging along as an ally, they discussed wether or not they should trust her. Soon the coven reached the [[Protection Witch Trial]].{{Ref|AAA104}}

====Protection Witch Trial====
The [[Agatha Harkness' Coven|coven]] spotted a [[Witches' Road Recording Studio|Recording Studio]], which made [[Alice Wu-Gulliver]] turn in the other direction. Wu-Gulliver did not want to enter, but the [[Witches' Road]] moved the house in front of them, forcing them to go inside. Once they entered, their clothes were once again changed, now influenced by the [[1970s]]. Due to [[Agatha Harkness]]'s trickery, the witches overheard Vidal stating that Harkness would kill them all and Vidal would collect their corpses, but their confrontation was interrupted by the teen starting a record of Lorna Wu's version of the "[[Ballad of the Witches' Road]]" that played backwards, transferring the [[Wu Family Curse]] onto the other members of the coven. Calderu was attacked first, then Kale. Wu-Gulliver recognized its effects after it struck Calderu and Kale, and she began apologizing for her involvement when the curse threw the teen through a glass pane, though he seemed largely unharmed. The group performed Lorna's rendition of [[Ballad of the Witches' Road]] after Wu-Gulliver realized that it was a protection spell, Kale played the bass during the performance. They were successful at killing the curse, passing the trial, but Teen passed out from his injury.

Returning to the Road, Harkness panicked over the teen's state, prompting Kale to perform a healing incantation, by using water and moonlight. Kale was able to save him just in time, provoking positive reactions from the group, specially Calderu who remarked it as a fascinating deed. Kale, Wu-Gulliver, Calderu, and Vidal bonded while Harkness watched over Teen, until Vidal and Harkness split from the group after Vidal alluded to their shared past. Calderu started a sentence and once again she stopped, Kale asked her where her mind went during these gaps, causing the group to laugh at Lilia's confusion.{{Ref|AAA104}}

====[[Ambush on Agatha Harkness' Coven]]====
The [[Agatha Harkness' Coven|coven]] rested on the road, but [[Lilia Calderu|Lilia]] suddenly woke up, revealing that the Salem Seven is in the vicinity, arriving on the road through a gate left open by the summoning spell that brought [[Rio Vidal]]. They confronted Harkness and Calderu explained to the group the Salem Seven's vendetta against the covenless witch. They moved, however they find themselves surrounded, [[Teen]] suggested they us a hexenbesen to escape. Kale bickered with the group, but with no other option, she paired up with Calderu to perform the ritual.

As they got prepared, [[Owl]] appeared, followed by the rest of the Seven. Luckily, the coven lifted off into the night sky. Their enjoyment was brief, as they were soon sucked back down towards the road. Although they crashed into [[Vertigo]], they were able to escape into the [[Witches' Road Cabin]].{{Ref|AAA105}}

====[[Spirit Witch Trial]]====
The [[Agatha Harkness' Coven|coven]] entered a [[Witches' Road Cabin|cabin]], which changed their clothes into pajamas. Harkness told them that they were safe from the [[Salem Seven]], so all they needed to do was complete the trial. [[Rio Vidal]] stated that they were in Harkness' trial. They figured out that they needed to commune to the dead, and [[Wiccan|Teen]] found a Ouija board, which started the trial.

Teen read out the rules, emphasizing the one about not taunting the dead. The coven gathered around the board, wondering who from Harkness' past they would be speaking with. Hesitantly, Harkness joined the coven but manipulated the board to make it seem like they were communing with the spirit of [[Sharon Davis]]. Harkness pretended to be possessed by Davis, speaking in her voice. Kale recognized that it was just Harkness stalling. Vidal called out Harkness for being scared, and she sat back down with the coven to use the board properly. The board said that it was "Death" and that it wanted to punish Harkness.

Harkness let go of the board, which flew off the table and released the spirit, posessing Harkness in the proccess. The coven discussed how they could punish Harkness, figuring that it would end the trial, Kale was fond of the idea and was choked by the possessed Harkness, until Calderu turned the lights back on and released the ghost. Harkness was freed from the possession, and the spirit introduced herself as [[Evanora Harkness]], she told the coven that they must complete the [[Witches' Road]] without Agatha. Kale wanted to leave but Agatha begged her to stay, so Evanora posessed Agatha again, when Wu-Gulliver stepped in to release Harkness from Evanora's control. Harkness ended up draining Wu-Gulliver's powers, killing her in the proccess.

The coven left the trial, with the exception of [[Death|Vidal]], Teen's identity is revealed by Harkness, enraged by her, he is the son of the [[Scarlet Witch]], [[Wiccan|Billy Maximoff]]. The teenager used his powers and took control over Kale and Calderu. The two dragged Harkness and threw her off the road. Once they were relseased from Maximoff's control, he threw them off the road as well. {{Ref|AAA105}}

====[[Divination Witch Trial]]====
Shortly after sinking in the mud, Kale and [[Lilia Calderu|Calderu]] found themselves in a tunnel system under the [[Witches' Road]]. Calderu woke up beforehand and exposed important information onto Kale, such as the identity of Teen and that they needed to find shelving in order to find the [[Witches' Road Castle|next]] [[Divination Witch Trial|trial]]. Kale was confused but figured she was telling the truth. The two encountered the way out of the Witches Road, but Lilia inspired her to keep going on, they quickly evade the [[Salem Seven]]. While making their way through the tunnels, Kale and Calderu bond, with Kale showing some interest and worry on Lilia's condition, Calderu explained that she experienced her life out of sequence. Eventually, Kale and Calderu overhear [[Agatha Harkness|voi]][[Wiccan|ces]] behind shelving. They push through the shelf and fall into the next [[Divination Witch Trial|trial]], which happened to be the Divination Trial.

The trial took place inside a castle and involved a Tarot spread, with swords dangling from the ceiling. Kale and Calderu arrived just in time, dressed up as ''The Evil Queen'' from ''Snow White'' and ''Glinda The Good Witch'' from ''The Wizard of Oz''. As Harkness and Maximoff caused the ceiling to lower, Kale spent the trial reassuring Calderu about her potential, after understading her better. However, swords still fell. After Calderu took a moment to collect herself, she reattempted the Tarot, but now on herself. As Calderu placed the cards, the ceiling continued to lower, forcing them all to crouch down with only seconds left until they were killed. Calderu realized that [[Rio Vidal]] was Death and told the group. The [[Salem Seven]] arrived, so they escaped from the castle. Kale refused to ley Lilia leave after her, but Calderu told Kale that she is the Path Ahead so she shut the door, much to Kale's disapproval.{{Ref|AAA107}}

====[[Green Witch Trial]]====
Following Lilia's sacrifice, Kale and [[Wiccan|Maximoff]] talk about [[Agatha Harkness|Agatha]] and [[Death|Rio]]'s relationship, Kale realized Vidal had told them her true identify from the start. They soon notice that they had been missing and went lloking for them. They regrouped with Harkness, Maximoff brought up how they didn't have their [[Green Witch]], but Harkness thought they would be fine. As Harkness hyped up the next trial, she tripped over the shoes they left at the beginning. Harkness was angered at this being the end, yelling at Maximoff for not knowing how to get out. Harkness decided to continue forwards, Kale argued back saying she would not be able to endure this experience again, but when Maximoff put his shoes on, he disappeared.

The three appeared in the next [[Witches' Road Morgue|trial]] inside of body bags. Once they got out, Kale noticed growing lights on the ceiling and suggested to Maximoff that they needed to grow something for the trial. As the countdown commenced, Harkness noticed Kale was calm, so she explained that she was thinking about how she could save Harkness and Maximoff. Harkness taunted Kale about having no [[magic]], Kale began talking about her past and soon realized that Harkness was the one who bound her. Maximoff angrily asked Harkness if it was true, but Harkness simply said she didn't know it was.

Kale was furious with Harkness, so she ripped out a piece of Harkness' hair and used it to begin the unbinding ritual. At first, Harkness was snarky towards Kale as she performed the ritual, but she soon became uncomfortable, seeing how she had hurt Kale. They then witnessed Kale reclaim her magic shortly before vanishing. 

In the morning, after succesfully surviving the Witches Road, Kale crawled out of the dirt in the outskirts of [[Westview]]. She took a moment to catch her breath and fled the scene with her powers.{{Ref|AAA108}}

==Powers and Abilities==
===Powers===
*'''[[Magic]]''': Kale was born a witch, allowing her to tap into the mystical forces of the universe and manipulate the world around her. Her specialty is in potions, and her powers come from alchemy.
**'''[[Magic#Witchcraft|Witchcraft]]''': As a witch, Jennifer had access to a specific kind of magic exclusive to witches known as witchcraft. Her magic manifests in the color of pink.
***'''Magical Energy Manipulation''': Jennifer was able to manipulate magical energy after unbinding.
****'''Levitation''': [[File:Jennifer Kale levitates into the sunset.png|thumb|250px|Kale levitates away from [[Westview]]]] Kale is able to use her powers to move through the air by holding her pink energy in her palms. She used this ability to leave [[Westview]] after her escape from the [[Witches' Road]].
***'''Spell Casting''': Jennifer can affect change in the physical world through spells. These spells are performed through certain hand gestures, incantations and chants. She performed a ritual to create a broomstick, giving it the ability to fly. Upon discovering that [[Agatha Harkness]] was the one who bound her, Kale was able to cast an unbinding spell and recover her magic.
***'''[[Magic#Alchemy|Alchemy]]''': Jennifer Kale is specialized in potions, and her powers come from alchemy and chemistry.
***'''Longevity''': As like many witches, Kale has the ability to live for far longer than an average human, whilst still retaining a youthful appearance. She has retained an adult appearance for over a hundred years.

===Abilities===
{{Quote|She saved my life. She saved you from [[Alewife's Revenge|poisoning]]. All while bound.|[[Billy Maximoff]] to [[Agatha Harkness]]|Follow Me My Friend / To Glory at the End}}
*'''Physician''': Using only water and moonlight, Kale was able to heal a grievous wound the [[Wu Family Curse]] had inflicted upon [[Billy Maximoff]], making it appear as if he had never been hurt.

